First off, I would like to say that if you can forage, brewing is so much easier.  To start out, make fish wine.  Combine a fish, grapes, water flask, and bottle in the brew barrel.  THis will take you to a skill of 62.  If you can forage, combine a vegetables with a water flask to make vegetable oil.  that will take you to 102, I think.  Next is 2 times dwarven brewed stout.  2 dwarven ale, 2short beer, and a cask in the brew barrel.  This will take you to 142.  If you can forage, I say make Ginesh, a vegetable, flask of water, shortbeer, and a shotglass until 168.  From here it is the Faydwer Shaker.  elven wine, dwarven ale, gnomish spirits, mead, and a cask.  The shaker will go until 188.  The final thing to make is the Minotaur hero brew, which will get you to 248.  It is made with 3 malts, 2short beers, 2 water flasks, a yeast, and a cask.  From there.  THat is it.  As far as I know, that is  the highest you can get without making brewer master sign.  (which is very expensive)

